<br>
Prior to PoP, mages weren't really known as good damage dealers. With rods, we could churn it out especially with rune items and FT10..<br>
<br>
Prior to PoP, monks were kick ass damage dealers.<br>
<br>
Post PoP, people are starting to notice just how good our damage dealing is, especially with FoT. People are starting to want mages in groups (PoJ trials are a good sign of this).<br>
<br>
So in relative terms, mages have had massive improvements recently. But then when we sucked so badly before, it's not that big an &quot;actual&quot; increase. <br>
<br>
Monks on the other hand went from being supertanks to random-death machines. So it's natural that they're lashing out at those who they perceive to have had massive gains in power. It's not right (no class should want any other class to be nerfed), but I can understand it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=broddathep>Brodda Thep</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(11/7/02 5:52:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=394.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Monks</span><hr size=1> There is a HUGE problem right now.<br>
<br>
Top end casters are being balanced against top end mellee.  Sounds good, right?  Sure fine and dandy.<br>
<br>
Problem is that if you compare a caster to a mellee that does NOT raid you will find a huge imbalance.<br>
<br>
Take a lvl 61 monk and a lvl 61 mage of the non-raiding variety.  Admittedly two of the extremes as far as suckiness and godliness outside of a raiding environment.<br>
<br>
Monk will be using a tranquil staff for the best damage.  Yes, this is about as good as it gets for a non-raiding monk.  <br>
<br>
Monk will be ok.  I imagine 3khp with full hp AAs.  Monk will probalby do 80dps against stuff like PoN goblins.  Now take that same mage.  He will probalby have FT4 at least.  Will be able to have mod rods.  Give weapons to pets (My shaman loves you guys!) Nuke for 2k damage for a piddly 500mana.  He will also have a pet that does 70dps.  Where the hell is the equality here?  <br>
<br>
A non-raiding caster can probalby reach 80-90% of their top effectiveness just through getting their lvl 61-64 spells and getting AAs.  A non-raiding mellee will probably reach 60-70% of their top end effectiveness just through getting AAs and equipment available to them at that level.<br>
<br>
Mages probably have it best of the casting classes in this regards and monks definately have it worse.  Warriors can get 12/19s with amazing proc.  Rogues get freebringer. (which lets them match my damage when I have a 15/18 and primal.)  Monks get tranquil staff.  And of course the plate tanks get that 50/45 in HoH.  Monks are absolutely dependent upon raids to be effective and yet they decided to nerf our tanking ability.  <br>
<br>
HELLO.  we lost our Pal the other day in PoN caves and I broke mez and the enchanter tanked from 100% to 30% health on the mob before I could get it on me.  And of course the sad thing is that the enchanter tanked better than me (Thanks ripostes for 400+) and just needed torpor so we didn't mem blur.  I am not a damn tank wihtout taunt or root.<br>
<br>
So yeah, you can see why monks are pretty pissed off.  ANd yes, I feel the casual caster is far too powerful compared to their raiding equivalent.  (This is a problem with decent caster itemization more than anything else.)<br>
<br>
For example I would rather two box my lvl 63 shaman in PoN caves than take many other shaman along even though he is still wearing some totemic.  Just because he has all of his good spells, has a horse, and I know I can play him well enough to make the trip through the caves safe.<br>
<br>
Of course this doesn't really affect me too much since I do have raid level gear on my monk.  I will probably make 5khp unbuffed and be wielding 1:1 or better ratio weapons by the end of PoP.  <br>
<br>
In the mean time I will continue (been doing this for a LONG time, except for the 61+ part) to snatch up any LFG 61+ mage I can get my hands on. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=broddathep>Brodda Thep</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(11/7/02 5:59:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=394.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Monks</span><hr size=1> BTW.  The point of my post is that non-raiding casters are coming far too close to their raiding equivalent while mellee will be left in the dust compared to their raiding equivalent.  <br>
<br>
This is bad and causes a large imbalance.  Of course this has been true for....  well just about forever. <br>
<br>
And it is amplifed by the fact that casters are advancing in power much faster than mellee in PoP.  I think alot of this will die down after a few more months into the expansion. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=milaru00>Milaru 00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#333333>(11/7/02 6:00:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=394.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Monks</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>  wizards, and any of the other snare/charm classes are the last people to be calling for a nerf. currently they are so powerful they dont even need to group at all <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
